{"id":91535,"title":"[Comprehensive rehabilitation of burn-induced dysfunctions in China].","abstract":"Burn patients often suffer from different degrees of dysfunction, such as residual burn wounds, formation of hyperplastic scar, scar itching, cardiopulmonary dysfunction, limitation of motion, and psychological disorders, which exert severe impact on their daily life. This article reviews various rehabilitation treatments for dysfunction after burn injury to promote rehabilitation of burn patients.","date":"2014-02-05","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24495638","annotations":[{"name":"China","weight":0.814578,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China"},{"name":"Injury","weight":0.787846,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Injury"},{"name":"Circulatory system","weight":0.728515,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circulatory_system"},{"name":"Burn","weight":0.691096,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burn"},{"name":"Scar","weight":0.687614,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scar"},{"name":"Mental disorder","weight":0.644462,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mental_disorder"},{"name":"Itch","weight":0.617472,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Itch"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.603856,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Psychology","weight":0.570603,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychology"},{"name":"Physical therapy","weight":0.474442,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physical_therapy"},{"name":"Hyperplasia","weight":0.172396,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyperplasia"},{"name":"Motion (physics)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motion_(physics)"},{"name":"Academic degree","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academic_degree"},{"name":"Formation (strat